Monica A McArthur is an instructor in the Department of Pediatrics, Division of Pediatric Infectious Diseases and Tropical Pediatrics and a member of the Center for Vaccine Development at the University of Maryland (UM; USA). She received a combined MD/PhD degree at The University of Texas Medical Branch (USA). Her primary interest is the interaction between pathogens and the human immune system.She is particularly interested in immune responses against infectious agents that affect children in the...

Marcelo B Sztein is Professor in the Departments of Pediatrics, Medicine and Microbiology, and Immunology at the UM, Associate Director for Immunologic Research, Leader of the Immunology Group, and Chief of the Cellular Immunology Section and Flow Cytometry Core Laboratory at the Center for Vaccine Development (at the UM). His research focuses on understanding the mechanisms underlying the generation of innate and protective adaptive immune responses to pathogens and vaccines in humans and animal models.

Robert Edelman is Clinical Professor of Medicine and Pediatrics, and Associate Director for Regulatory Affairs and Bioethics at the Center for Vaccine Development. He received his MD degree from Washington University (USA). He has served as Senior Consultant on vaccine development to industry, government and private foundations at the UM since 1988, and has served as Lead Investigator on clinical trials of vaccines or biologicals in volunteers against a wide variety of infectious diseases.
